to directly fund the games we want. The importance

00:06:21.069 --> 00:06:24.729
of this cannot be stressed more than by this
Banjo and Kazooie spiritual successor. In

00:06:24.729 --> 00:06:30.940
a new Banjo game, people wanted a 3D platformer
with a big world full of collectibles to explore,

00:06:30.940 --> 00:06:35.860
but after 10 years of waiting Microsoft gave
us a god damn build your own car game. But

00:06:35.860 --> 00:06:41.020
alas, people power has saved the day. Yooka
Laylee is going to be a 3D platformer with

00:06:41.020 --> 00:06:45.650
a big world full of collectibles and cartoony
characters. It's going to reek of the 90's

00:06:45.650 --> 00:06:50.500
and early 3D gaming and that is exactly what
the people who funded this record Kickstarter

00:06:50.500 --> 00:06:54.500
want. Perhaps the most important part to this
project is that it's being made by golden

00:06:54.500 --> 00:06:59.340
age Rare employees who have collaborated before
and are truly passionate about making this

00:06:59.340 --> 00:07:03.449
game. Not to mention, the proof that these
guys still have what it takes goes beyond

00:07:03.449 --> 00:07:08.430
their logic of making the game players want.
Their trademark humour, best exhibited in

00:07:08.430 --> 00:07:12.300
Conker, is already on display in the form
of Yooka Laylee's newest character Trowzer.

00:07:12.300 --> 00:07:18.300
He's a snake wearing trousers; literally a
trouser snake. In Yooka Laylee, we trust.

